requests.title: Re-activate Resource Sharing Features for Charged Items

comments.body:
Here is screen capture of the old code running on borrow direct:
![Screen Shot 2020-09-10 at 11 55 38 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1599081/92770314-d0e3ea00-f367-11ea-8ff4-553247e11989.png)
Gem used to interact with API from our Borrow Direct system: https://github.com/jrochkind/borrow_direct.

This route was used via AJAX by the form to search BD for a direct match via standard number, https://github.com/pulibrary/requests/blob/master/config/routes.rb#L3. If that failed the screenshot above would appear. If it succeeded the form would be set-up to allow the user to submit a direct request for the item to Borrow Direct. The borrow direct system handles the patron notification so we would generate no emails on our side when a user would select that option.
